    {
      "id": 60,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Each concept builds on the others. The Five Powers require the AI Stack. Digital FTEs require AIFF Standards to be portable. Spec-Driven Development is how you direct them.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 105,
      "line_end": 106,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "The Multiplier Effect",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 107,
      "line_end": 108,
      "context": "heading_h2"
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Before you move on, understand this:",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 109,
      "line_end": 110,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 63,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Everything you learn in this book compounds.**",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 111,
      "line_end": 112,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 64,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Clear specifications make AI execution precise",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 113,
      "line_end": 114,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 65,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Precise execution enables reliable Custom Agents",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 114,
      "line_end": 115,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 66,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Reliable Custom Agents become Digital FTEs",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 115,
      "line_end": 116,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Digital FTEs multiply your capacity",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 116,
      "line_end": 117,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Multiplied capacity lets you tackle larger problems",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 117,
      "line_end": 118,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Larger problems require even better specifications",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 118,
      "line_end": 119,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 70,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "This is a virtuous cycle. The developers who master specification-first thinking will build capabilities that developers stuck in Vibe Coding cannot match.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 120,
      "line_end": 121,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 71,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "The gap will widen with every generation of AI tools.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 122,
      "line_end": 123,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 72,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Your Choice",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 124,
      "line_end": 125,
      "context": "heading_h2"
    },
    {
      "id": 73,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "You've seen the evidence. You understand the paradigm. You know the difference between tools and teammates, between Vibe Coding and Spec-Driven Development.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 126,
      "line_end": 127,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 74,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Now you choose:",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 128,
      "line_end": 129,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 75,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Path A**: Treat AI as a faster keyboard. Vibe Code your way through projects. Generate code quickly without clear specifications. Watch technical debt compound while competitors build systematic capabilities.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 130,
      "line_end": 131,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 76,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Path B**: Master the Agent Factory paradigm. Write clear specifications. Build Digital FTEs that reliably handle specialized functions. Multiply your capacity systematically.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 132,
      "line_end": 133,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 77,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "This book teaches Path B.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 134,
      "line_end": 135,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 78,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Chapter Summary",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 136,
      "line_end": 137,
      "context": "heading_h2"
    },
    {
      "id": 79,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "In this chapter, you learned:",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 138,
      "line_end": 139,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 80,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**The 2025 Inflection Point** (Lesson 1): Concrete evidence that AI coding reached production quality—ICPC perfect scores, 84% developer adoption, $3 trillion economy transformation.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 140,
      "line_end": 141,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 81,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Three Core Operational Constraints of LLMs** (Lesson 2): LLMs are stateless (no memory between sessions), probabilistic (variable outputs from identical inputs), and context-limited (finite working memory). These constraints explain why methodologies like SDD, AGENTS.md, and context engineering exist.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 142,
      "line_end": 143,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 82,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**From Coder to Orchestrator** (Lesson 3): Your role shifts from typing code to directing AI. The 10% you contribute—judgment, specifications, validation—becomes infinitely more valuable.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 144,
      "line_end": 145,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 83,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**The Five Powers & AI Stack** (Lesson 4): Agents combine See, Hear, Reason, Act, and Remember via a three-layer stack (Frontier Models → AI-First IDEs → Development Agents) connected by MCP.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 146,
      "line_end": 147,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 84,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**AIFF Standards Foundation** (Lesson 5): The governance body and three standards (AGENTS.md, Agent Skills, MCP) that make agents portable, reliable, and interoperable.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 148,
      "line_end": 149,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 85,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Digital FTE Business Strategy** (Lesson 6): How specialized AI agents map to business roles, their cost structure compared to humans, and the strategic advantages they offer.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 150,
      "line_end": 151,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 86,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Nine Pillars of AI-Native Design** (Lesson 7): Design principles from intent-based UI to progressive disclosure that define the AI-Native Development paradigm.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 152,
      "line_end": 153,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 87,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Spec-Driven Development** (Lesson 8): The four-phase methodology (specify → clarify → plan → implement) that makes AI collaboration effective.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 154,
      "line_end": 155,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 88,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**The Digital FTE Vision** (this lesson): Custom Agents and General Agents can become Digital Full-Time Employees. AI amplifies your habits—so discipline matters more, not less.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 156,
      "line_end": 157,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 89,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Selling Agentic AI Services** (Lesson 10): The $100-400 billion market opportunity, enterprise buying patterns, four value propositions, and outcome-based pricing models for selling your Digital FTE solutions.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 158,
      "line_end": 159,
      "context": "list_item"
    },
    {
      "id": 90,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "You now have the mental models for AI-native development—and the business strategy to monetize them.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 160,
      "line_end": 161,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 91,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Next**: Lesson 10: Selling Agentic AI Services teaches you how to bring your Digital FTE capabilities to market, covering enterprise sales positioning, the four value propositions, and outcome-based commercial models.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 162,
      "line_end": 163,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 92,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Try With AI",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 164,
      "line_end": 165,
      "context": "heading_h2"
    },
    {
      "id": 93,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Reflection Exercise**",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 166,
      "line_end": 167,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 94,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Ask Claude Code (or your preferred AI assistant):",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 168,
      "line_end": 169,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 95,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**What you're learning:** Connecting abstract concepts to your actual work patterns. This reflection helps you identify where Spec-Driven Development will have the biggest impact on your current projects.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 185,
      "line_end": 186,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 96,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Synthesis Exercise**",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 187,
      "line_end": 188,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 97,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "Ask Claude Code:",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 189,
      "line_end": 190,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 98,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**What you're learning:** How the chapter's concepts integrate in practice. This synthesis exercise shows you how to apply the mental model to a real Digital FTE you might build.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 208,
      "line_end": 209,
      "context": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "id": 99,
      "type": "inline",
      "original": "**Note**: Start with non-sensitive projects. Review changes before accepting.",
      "translated": "",
      "line_start": 210,
